title: Miso Ramen 味噌ラーメン
summary: The recipe Miso Ramen 味噌ラーメン is ready in about 25 minutes and is definitely an amazing dairy free option for lovers of Japanese food. One serving contains 620 calories, 26g of protein, and 35g of fat. For $3.83 per serving, this recipe covers 26% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Several people made this recipe, and 180 would say it hit the spot. If you have ginger, ground pork, sesame oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the sugar you could follow this main course with the Whole Wheat Refined Sugar Free Sugar Cookies as a dessert. It works well as a rather expensive main course. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 81%. This score is tremendous. Try Cooking School: Miso Ramen with Miso Glazed Chicken, Enoki and Shimeji Mushrooms, Miso Ramen, and Miso ramen for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Ramen Noodles works really well with Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. You could try Blue Fish Sweet Riesling. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.8 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 13 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Blue Fish Sweet Riesling
productMatches.description:
Pale gold. Seductive perfume of fresh apricot, peaches, and ripe pineapple. Fruity sweetness with a full-bodied structure and refreshing acidity.
Complements shellfish, mussels, Asian-inspired cuisine, and mild cheeses.

instructions: Mince the garlic, ginger, and shallot.Grind sesame seeds.In a medium pot, heat sesame oil over medium heat and cook the minced garlic, ginger, and shallot until fragrant.Add the meat and increase heat to medium high. Cook the meat until no longer pink.Add spicy bean paste (La Doubanjiang) and miso.And add sesame seeds and sugar and mix well.Add sake, chicken stock, salt and pepper.Keep the ramen soup simmered.Noodles will be done cooking in less than 2 minutes. Therefore, prepare ramen toppings first so you can serve the hot ramen immediately.Bring a large pot of un-salted water to a boil (ramen noodles already have salt in the dough) While boiling, take some hot water into serving bowls to warm up the bowls. Loosen up the noodles and cook according to the package instructions. I usually cook the noodles al dente (about 15 seconds earlier than suggested time).When noodles are done, quickly pick them up with a mesh sieve. You dont want to dilute your soup, so make sure you drain the water well. Serve the noodles into bowls.Add the soup and top with various toppings youve prepared. I put chashu, ramen egg, spicy bean sprout salad, corn, scallion, shiraga negi, pickled red ginger, and a sheet of nori.
